00:15:33.922 --> 00:15:35.173
<i>You should have let it go.</i>

259
00:15:36.716 --> 00:15:37.841
<i>But you didn't let it go.</i>

260
00:15:39.302 --> 00:15:41.386
<i>You didn't like that someone told you no.</i>

261
00:15:42.346 --> 00:15:44.890
<i>'Cause guys like you
get anything you want. right?</i>

262
00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:51.773
You're home early.

263
00:15:55.692 --> 00:15:56.527
Hey.

264
00:15:57.110 --> 00:15:58.571
Come sit with me a minute.

265
00:16:12.961 --> 00:16:14.379
This isn't a talk. is it?

266
00:16:14.836 --> 00:16:16.089
No talk.

267
00:16:17.130 --> 00:16:19.008
We'll communicate through semaphores.

268
00:16:20.717 --> 00:16:24.096
I can see how you'd think I'd be the
one person to laugh at that. but...

269
00:16:25.347 --> 00:16:26.349
Where's your bike?

270
00:16:28.518 --> 00:16:29.519
Uh...

271
00:16:30.019 --> 00:16:32.522
I uh... messed up the crank...

272
00:16:33.355 --> 00:16:35.441
so I left it with Tony. to fix it.

273
00:16:38.820 --> 00:16:39.736
Listen.

274
00:16:41.029 --> 00:16:42.865
About what you heard this morning.

275
00:16:42.990 --> 00:16:44.366
I didn't hear anything.

276
00:16:44.866 --> 00:16:47.036
Well. if you did...

277
00:16:48.788 --> 00:16:49.706
your mom and I...

278
00:16:52.290 --> 00:16:53.918
we disagree on some things.

279
00:16:54.251 --> 00:16:55.878
I didn't hear anything. Dad.

280
00:16:57.129 --> 00:16:58.005
Honest.

281
00:16:58.673 --> 00:17:00.674
She thinks maybe you're having
nightmares again.

282
00:17:06.346 --> 00:17:07.347
And if you are...

283
00:17:08.057 --> 00:17:10.143
and if you want
to talk to someone about them.

284
00:17:10.225 --> 00:17:12.394
someone who doesn't share your DNA...

285
00:17:13.020 --> 00:17:14.480
I'll... I'll let you know.

286
00:17:19.152 --> 00:17:21.194
Look. I hated high school.

287
00:17:22.613 --> 00:17:23.990
I couldn't wait to get out.

288
00:17:24.740 --> 00:17:26.534
It was hell for me.

289
00:17:28.952 --> 00:17:30.078
I was a target...

290
00:17:31.622 --> 00:17:33.040
more than once.

291
00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:36.376
Shit.

292
00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:38.171
I'm sorry. Dad.

293
00:17:38.587 --> 00:17:39.588
But I survived.

294
00:17:41.214 --> 00:17:42.383
And look at me now.

295
00:17:42.884 --> 00:17:44.384
I'm a paragon of manhood.

296
00:17:46.471 --> 00:17:48.306
With a fucking beautiful family.

297
00:17:51.517 --> 00:17:52.351
Yeah.

298
00:17:53.185 --> 00:17:54.228
You did all right.

299
00:17:56.271 --> 00:17:57.440
What I'm saying...

300
00:17:58.732 --> 00:18:00.026
I had things to hang on to.

301
00:18:00.108 --> 00:18:01.486
I had chess club.

302
00:18:01.568 --> 00:18:02.569
I had Knowledge Bowl...

303
00:18:02.653 --> 00:18:04.404
See. now you're
embarrassing yourself. Dad.

304
00:18:04.905 --> 00:18:06.115
Do you have something?

305
00:18:07.075 --> 00:18:09.493
Does anything bring you joy?

306
00:18:11.328 --> 00:18:12.371
Or just relief?

307
00:18:15.083 --> 00:18:18.211
Your mom and I would feel
so much better if you had something...

308
00:18:20.462 --> 00:18:22.882
if you took more of an interest in.
you know...

309
00:18:23.673 --> 00:18:25.175
school activities.

310
00:18:27.095 --> 00:18:28.136
You know...

311
00:18:29.888 --> 00:18:32.474
I was actually thinking of going
to the basketball game tonight...

312
00:18:33.101 --> 00:18:34.143
believe it or not.

313
00:18:35.728 --> 00:18:36.813
I have. uh...

314
00:18:38.564 --> 00:18:39.523
a friend playing.

315
00:18:53.121 --> 00:18:55.455
<i>Maybe you think you deserve
everything you get...</i>

316
00:18:56.749 --> 00:18:57.750
<i>and more.</i>

317
00:18:58.792 --> 00:19:01.295
<i>Maybe you're just used to hearing
the cheers of the crowd.</i>

318
00:19:20.690 --> 00:19:21.648
Clay.

319
00:19:22.858 --> 00:19:23.984
What are you doing here?

320
00:19:24.777 --> 00:19:27.154
It's a basketball game.
I'm here to show some school spirit.

321
00:19:28.405 --> 00:19:29.281
That's great.

322
00:19:29.699 --> 00:19:30.657
Great. Clay.

323
00:19:31.075 --> 00:19:32.326
I'm glad you're. you know...

324
00:19:33.411 --> 00:19:34.494
feeling better.

325
00:19:34.744 --> 00:19:35.663
Hey.

326
00:19:36.955 --> 00:19:37.832
How's it going?

327
00:19:38.708 --> 00:19:40.250
Everything's great. Marcus.

328
00:19:40.960 --> 00:19:42.711
What the fuck are you doing here. dude?

329
00:19:42.795 --> 00:19:43.921
What's your play now?

330
00:19:44.713 --> 00:19:45.714
Hey. guys.

331
00:19:46.507 --> 00:19:47.633
Can I get a picture?

332
00:19:48.009 --> 00:19:50.010
Nothing's going on. Tyler. Just go away.

333
00:19:50.094 --> 00:19:52.305
I seriously just wanted
a picture for the yearbook.

334
00:19:52.512 --> 00:19:54.598
If they knew the kind of pictures
you really took!

335
00:19:54.682 --> 00:19:55.682
Hey.

336
00:19:55.766 --> 00:19:57.476
These T-shirts look great.

337
00:19:57.977 --> 00:19:59.854
Uh. I'm glad you approve. Mr. Porter.

338
00:20:00.188 --> 00:20:02.565
I appreciate all the hard work
you guys put into it.

339
00:20:02.815 --> 00:20:03.900
Mr. Down...

340
00:20:04.442 --> 00:20:06.484
would you get a picture of us
for the yearbook?

341
00:20:07.569 --> 00:20:08.570
Yeah.

342
00:20:09.404 --> 00:20:10.239
Yeah.

343
00:20:28.173 --> 00:20:30.593
Clay. what are you doing?
Get off the court.

344
00:20:31.009 --> 00:20:32.803
Jensen. get off the fucking court.

345
00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:37.016
What the hell. Jensen?

346
00:20:37.098 --> 00:20:38.351
Game's about to start.

347
00:20:42.020 --> 00:20:44.022
Hey. you! Get off the court!

348
00:20:47.526 --> 00:20:49.028
Get off the court. Go.

349
00:20:49.111 --> 00:20:50.904
Hey. skinny kid.
get the hell off the court.

350
00:20:56.035 --> 00:20:57.452
Clay. you okay?

351
00:20:58.788 --> 00:20:59.829
Do you care?

352
00:21:03.584 --> 00:21:04.961
Where the hell's Jessica?

353
00:21:05.752 --> 00:21:06.753
She texted me.

354
00:21:06.836 --> 00:21:08.673
She was babysitting her brothers

355
00:21:08.756 --> 00:21:10.967
and had to wait
till her mom got home to leave.

356
00:21:11.925 --> 00:21:13.301
Well. we can't wait for her.

357
00:21:13.844 --> 00:21:16.221
Okay. ladies. let's go!

358
00:21:18.766 --> 00:21:22.060
<i>Maybe you can't imagine what it
feels like to be on the sidelines. Zach...</i>

359
00:21:23.354 --> 00:21:24.563
<i>like most of us are.</i>

360
00:21:33.071 --> 00:21:36.366
<i>You can't imagine why a little
piece of paper could mean so much.</i>

361
00:21:41.079 --> 00:21:43.249
Um. everybody. before you leave.

362
00:21:43.332 --> 00:21:46.836
we've added an anonymous
class discussion bag to the racks.

363
00:21:46.919 --> 00:21:49.547
We're gonna check it every Friday
and talk it over.

364
00:21:53.009 --> 00:21:54.719
You got another bunny?

365
00:21:55.802 --> 00:21:57.096
I wish I would get one.

366
00:21:57.179 --> 00:21:58.513
Still don't know who they're from?

367
00:22:03.102 --> 00:22:04.936
You got. like. six compliments today.

368
00:22:05.186 --> 00:22:08.023
I got a cartoon
and a campaign flyer from Courtney.

369
00:22:08.106 --> 00:22:09.191
Yeah.

370
00:22:10.067 --> 00:22:13.112
You do realize shilling for votes
is not a compliment. Courtney.

371
00:22:14.113 --> 00:22:15.614
I'm sorry you feel that way. Skye.

372
00:22:15.698 --> 00:22:18.951
but I'm proud of my efforts.
and I wanted to share that with the class.

373
00:22:37.344 --> 00:22:38.345
Hey. Clay.

374
00:22:39.888 --> 00:22:41.182
Go away. Tyler.

375
00:22:41.932 --> 00:22:43.476
You know. I get that a lot.

376
00:22:43.893 --> 00:22:45.685
Especially lately. But today I'm on...

377
00:22:46.519 --> 00:22:48.939
official yearbook business.

378
00:22:52.442 --> 00:22:53.943
Why are you even talking to me?

379
00:22:55.237 --> 00:22:57.114
Because I want to see
what you're gonna do next.

380
00:22:57.698 --> 00:23:00.201
You really messed Courtney up.
Not as much as you did to me.

381
00:23:00.910 --> 00:23:01.911
Still...

382
00:23:02.619 --> 00:23:03.746
the cemetery?

383
00:23:04.204 --> 00:23:05.205
That's cold.

384
00:23:07.540 --> 00:23:09.085
Does everybody know about that?

385
00:23:10.001 --> 00:23:11.836
Everybody knows about everything.

386
00:23:12.296 --> 00:23:13.672
They know about your nightmares.

387
00:23:13.756 --> 00:23:15.673
They know you beat off
to Hannah's picture.

388
00:23:16.174 --> 00:23:17.675
And they know what you did to her.

389
00:23:20.762 --> 00:23:21.763
What is it?

390
00:23:23.182 --> 00:23:24.349
What did I do?

391
00:23:26.227 --> 00:23:27.228
What?

392
00:23:30.396 --> 00:23:31.397
Clay?

393
00:23:35.111 --> 00:23:36.112
Heads up.

394
00:23:40.574 --> 00:23:42.326
Jensen. come on. throw the damn ball.

395
00:23:43.786 --> 00:23:44.787
Clay.

396
00:23:46.997 --> 00:23:48.540
- Clay.
- Come on!

397
00:23:48.874 --> 00:23:50.875
Come on. what are you waiting for?

398
00:23:51.626 --> 00:23:53.170
Throw the ball. dipshit.

399
00:23:55.172 --> 00:23:56.882
Jesus. Clay. what the fuck?

400
00:23:59.009 --> 00:24:00.009
Clay.

401
00:24:01.679 --> 00:24:02.512
Clay.

402
00:24:03.806 --> 00:24:05.849
- Clay.
- We got a game. man!

403
00:24:06.016 --> 00:24:07.643
Throw it in. loser!

404
00:24:10.938 --> 00:24:12.314
Thanks for making me do that.

405
00:24:18.820 --> 00:24:20.029
Uh-uh. No way.

406
00:24:20.573 --> 00:24:22.490
You've been late to practice
twice this week.

407
00:24:22.782 --> 00:24:24.785
Now you miss most of first quarter?

408
00:24:25.035 --> 00:24:27.203
I'm sorry.
I didn't know I was going to be so late.

409
00:24:27.621 --> 00:24:30.039
Jess. look. you got a problem.

410
00:24:30.124 --> 00:24:31.875
come to me. we'll work it out.

411
00:24:32.334 --> 00:24:34.711
But I'm sorry. you're out of today's game.

412
00:24:46.723 --> 00:24:47.892
Yo. Jess.

413
00:24:48.017 --> 00:24:49.143
You're not leaving. are you?

414
00:24:49.226 --> 00:24:50.728
I'm benched for the game.

415
00:24:50.978 --> 00:24:53.271
Or didn't the entire gym just hear that?

416
00:24:53.480 --> 00:24:54.940
Well. if you're benched. take a seat.

417
00:24:55.023 --> 00:24:57.108
- Make some room. you guys.
- I don't know.

418
00:24:57.942 --> 00:25:00.362
Come on. you don't want to miss
your boyfriend's big game.

419
00:25:01.070 --> 00:25:02.072
And...

420
00:25:02.364 --> 00:25:03.824
we're having fun up there.

421
00:25:11.499 --> 00:25:12.708
Milady.

422
00:25:12.790 --> 00:25:15.752
<i>Maybe you don't know what
it's like to need a lifeline. Zach.</i>

423
00:25:25.596 --> 00:25:28.223
<i>The day after you insulted me
in the cafeteria.</i>

424
00:25:28.307 --> 00:25:30.226
<i>my compliment bag was empty.</i>

425
00:25:32.728 --> 00:25:34.104
<i>Not even a cute bunny.</i>

426
00:25:36.606 --> 00:25:38.858
<i>By the end of the second week.
I knew something was up.</i>

427
00:25:47.576 --> 00:25:50.119
<i>Maybe I should have let it go.
but I didn't.</i>

428
00:25:50.954 --> 00:25:52.205
<i>I wrote you a letter.</i>

429
00:25:52.705 --> 00:25:54.124
<i>I poured my heart out.</i>

430
00:25:54.208 --> 00:25:56.085
<i>opening up about personal things</i>

431
00:25:56.167 --> 00:25:58.336
<i>I hadn't had the courage
to admit to anyone:</i>

432
00:25:58.586 --> 00:26:00.422
<i>How hard life was getting...</i>

433
00:26:00.964 --> 00:26:02.423
<i>how lonely I felt...</i>

434
00:26:02.883 --> 00:26:06.052
<i>and how those stupid compliments
actually meant something to me.</i>

435
00:26:15.561 --> 00:26:16.771
<i>And then I set my trap.</i>

436
00:27:08.115 --> 00:27:10.742
<i>I was hoping once you read
the letter. you'd get it.</i>

437
00:27:10.826 --> 00:27:14.163
<i>you'd realize how much I needed those
silly things you were stealing from me.</i>

438
00:27:18.208 --> 00:27:20.294
<i>But I guess I wasn't even
worth a reaction.</i>

439
00:27:24.714 --> 00:27:25.798
Why me. Zach?

440
00:27:27.259 --> 00:27:28.344
Why me?

441
00:27:41.690 --> 00:27:43.692
Wow. that's double digits already.

442
00:28:05.798 --> 00:28:06.798
Jeez.

443
00:28:06.882 --> 00:28:08.717
Zach is on fire tonight.

444
00:28:13.721 --> 00:28:14.722
Whoo!

445
00:28:16.682 --> 00:28:19.019
Zach! Zach! Zach! Zach!

446
00:28:31.573 --> 00:28:32.907
Zach! Zach!

447
00:28:35.993 --> 00:28:40.289
Oh-ho-ho-ho! Yeah!

448
00:28:50.675 --> 00:28:51.676
Stop it!

449
00:28:51.759 --> 00:28:52.845
Stop! Stop it!

450
00:28:52.927 --> 00:28:54.555
Stop playing! Stop the game! Stop!

451
00:28:54.762 --> 00:28:56.432
Stop it! Stop. stop!

452
00:29:05.816 --> 00:29:07.108
Is he crazy?

453
00:29:21.123 --> 00:29:22.374
<i>Why me. Zach?</i>

454
00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:24.209
<i>Why me?</i>

455
00:29:52.863 --> 00:29:54.448
Stickin' it to the man!

456
00:29:55.574 --> 00:29:58.951
Or. you know. one particular man
who's rich enough and fucked-up enough

457
00:29:59.036 --> 00:30:01.329
to get his asshole son a $60.000 car.

458
00:30:02.079 --> 00:30:03.457
Skye. what are you...

459
00:30:03.749 --> 00:30:05.041
Are you at the game?

460
00:30:05.459 --> 00:30:06.501
God. no!

461
00:30:08.711 --> 00:30:09.837
Sculpture studio.

462
00:30:10.213 --> 00:30:13.133
It's the only time I can get
the welding rig away from the shop boys.

463
00:30:15.844 --> 00:30:16.970
Were you at the game?

464
00:30:18.888 --> 00:30:19.890
I was.

465
00:30:20.682 --> 00:30:23.143
But it was so bad.
you had to leave before halftime?

466
00:30:27.314 --> 00:30:28.315
I can't...

467
00:30:30.233 --> 00:30:31.567
I can't do this anymore.

468
00:30:33.319 --> 00:30:34.320
This goddamn school.

469
00:30:34.403 --> 00:30:35.614
it's a terrible place.

470
00:30:36.114 --> 00:30:38.491
You're just now coming
to this realization?

471
00:30:39.701 --> 00:30:42.203
Where have you been for
the past three years?

472
00:30:43.830 --> 00:30:44.998
Oh. that's right.

473
00:30:45.082 --> 00:30:46.458
pining after a pretty dead girl.

474
00:30:49.126 --> 00:30:50.045
Why are you so mean?

475
00:30:51.838 --> 00:30:53.298
I thought we were friends.

476
00:30:54.924 --> 00:30:55.925
Were.

477
00:30:56.926 --> 00:30:58.177
We were friends.

478
00:30:59.805 --> 00:31:00.972
What happened?

479
00:31:02.516 --> 00:31:03.683
I didn't understand it.

480
00:31:04.268 --> 00:31:05.477
I still don't.

481
00:31:05.853 --> 00:31:07.770
Yeah. well. welcome to the world.

482
00:31:07.855 --> 00:31:09.064
Well. I hate it.

483
00:31:09.772 --> 00:31:10.773
Me too.

484
00:31:17.196 --> 00:31:20.867
I like this new... angry.
Audi-keying Clay.

485
00:31:22.411 --> 00:31:23.494
He's got spunk.

486
00:31:25.955 --> 00:31:27.374
I think I'm losing my shit.

487
00:31:28.165 --> 00:31:29.542
Shit's overrated.

488
00:31:30.626 --> 00:31:31.627
Lose it.

489
00:31:36.340 --> 00:31:38.259
I'm gonna be in so much trouble.

490
00:31:39.135 --> 00:31:40.721
Not if no one knows you did it.

491
00:31:41.846 --> 00:31:42.890
You won't tell?

492
00:31:43.265 --> 00:31:45.057
Please. why would I tell?

493
00:31:48.019 --> 00:31:49.938
I think it needs a question mark.

494
00:32:10.875 --> 00:32:11.876
Oh. shit.

495
00:32:12.251 --> 00:32:13.670
Halftime. I should go.

496
00:32:13.921 --> 00:32:15.005
I'll see you around?

497
00:32:15.297 --> 00:32:16.548
Seems likely.

498
00:32:21.219 --> 00:32:22.220
Hey. Clay.

499
00:32:23.721 --> 00:32:24.722
Stay angry.

500
00:32:27.893 --> 00:32:29.394
<i>I was feeling desperate.</i>

501
00:32:29.478 --> 00:32:31.438
<i>so I texted someone
I thought was a friend.</i>

502
00:32:32.480 --> 00:32:34.148
His Audi? You...

503
00:32:34.650 --> 00:32:36.484
you don't fuck with another dude's car.

504
00:32:36.567 --> 00:32:37.903
I know. I know. I just...

505
00:32:40.113 --> 00:32:41.365
I listened to his tape.

506
00:32:43.200 --> 00:32:44.742
And he just got away with everything.

507
00:32:44.826 --> 00:32:46.827
And he scored. like. 30 points tonight.

508
00:32:46.912 --> 00:32:48.829
You keyed his car
'cause he scored 30 points?

509
00:32:48.913 --> 00:32:51.165
No. because it's not fair. Tony.

510
00:32:52.125 --> 00:32:53.542
It's not fucking fair.

511
00:32:57.297 --> 00:32:58.839
Those tapes are messing me up.

512
00:33:00.509 --> 00:33:02.927
- They're doing shit to my head.
- I get it. I get it.

513
00:33:03.511 --> 00:33:04.596
I don't think you do.

514
00:33:04.680 --> 00:33:06.431
I do. Believe me.

515
00:33:06.722 --> 00:33:08.307
This is all so easy for you.

516
00:33:08.642 --> 00:33:10.309
You don't know what you're talking about.

517
00:33:10.394 --> 00:33:11.560
Then tell me.

518
00:33:13.896 --> 00:33:15.731
You seem like a tall vanilla latte.

519
00:33:16.692 --> 00:33:17.692
I mean. for a drink.

520
00:33:20.237 --> 00:33:21.238
Thanks.

521
00:33:21.320 --> 00:33:22.405
I was just leaving.

522
00:33:23.906 --> 00:33:24.907
Clay.

523
00:33:25.826 --> 00:33:27.576
You're going to get through this.

