Yes. Clay.

784
00:48:12.920 --> 00:48:15.255
How important was it to you
to help Hannah Baker?

785
00:48:18.050 --> 00:48:20.760
Extremely important to me. Clay.
Why do you ask?

786
00:48:23.389 --> 00:48:25.724
Remember that note you got
in your bag last year?

787
00:48:27.393 --> 00:48:29.353
The one about
not feeling anything anymore?

788
00:48:33.773 --> 00:48:34.942
It was from Hannah.

789
00:48:37.110 --> 00:48:39.487
Okay. uh. why do you think that is?

790
00:48:41.907 --> 00:48:42.907
- Mrs. Bradley?
- Yes?

791
00:48:42.992 --> 00:48:45.077
Sorry to interrupt.
but I need Mr. Jensen.

792
00:48:45.702 --> 00:48:46.996
Okay. Mr. Porter.

793
00:48:47.079 --> 00:48:49.664
Clay. we can continue this
discussion at another time.

794
00:48:51.626 --> 00:48:53.418
I have to say. I'm a little surprised.

795
00:48:54.336 --> 00:48:55.378
What? Why?

796
00:48:55.713 --> 00:48:56.922
I know it's been a few weeks.

797
00:48:57.005 --> 00:48:59.634
but you seem like the type of kid
to follow through on a promise.

798
00:49:00.760 --> 00:49:01.802
Don't worry. Clay.

799
00:49:02.135 --> 00:49:03.804
I almost forgot too.

800
00:49:04.889 --> 00:49:05.972
Forgot what?

801
00:49:06.056 --> 00:49:08.809
Courtney and Clay. these are
our new foreign exchange students

802
00:49:08.893 --> 00:49:10.728
joining us this semester.

803
00:49:10.936 --> 00:49:15.231
This is Jhene. Fynn.
Mahla and Deep.

804
00:49:15.398 --> 00:49:18.027
Uh. Courtney and Clay
will be helping you out.

805
00:49:18.110 --> 00:49:20.905
They are on the Honor Board
and they'll be giving you the tour.

806
00:49:21.237 --> 00:49:22.530
The insider's tour!

807
00:49:22.782 --> 00:49:25.201
All the secrets that you need to know.

808
00:49:28.204 --> 00:49:29.496
Okay. great.

809
00:49:32.958 --> 00:49:34.043
<i>So as you can see.</i>

810
00:49:34.126 --> 00:49:36.920
it's one of the finest high school
parking lots in the world.

811
00:49:37.420 --> 00:49:38.797
Oh. and right here is the library.

812
00:49:38.880 --> 00:49:42.550
where you can find books and tables
and chairs and all that stuff...

813
00:49:42.967 --> 00:49:44.219
state-of-the-art computers.

814
00:49:44.302 --> 00:49:46.304
at least if the art was ten years ago...

815
00:49:46.639 --> 00:49:47.764
and friendly librarians.

816
00:49:47.931 --> 00:49:50.768
Not super bright always. but friendly.

817
00:49:54.271 --> 00:49:55.815
Oh. wait. everyone.

818
00:49:56.065 --> 00:49:58.733
It's Justin Foley and Zach Dempsey.

819
00:49:58.818 --> 00:50:00.777
star basketball players
here at Liberty High.

820
00:50:00.860 --> 00:50:03.197
Hey. Justin. where's my bike?

821
00:50:03.614 --> 00:50:04.739
Justin stole my bike.

822
00:50:05.324 --> 00:50:06.784
What the fuck?
What are you doing?

823
00:50:06.867 --> 00:50:08.869
I'm giving our new
foreign exchange students a tour.

824
00:50:08.952 --> 00:50:11.329
Figured they should know
who owns the school. right. you guys?

825
00:50:11.414 --> 00:50:12.414
Clay.

826
00:50:12.539 --> 00:50:13.833
Right. right. Moving on.

827
00:50:13.958 --> 00:50:14.958
Where were we?

828
00:50:15.041 --> 00:50:16.043
Right. The auditorium.

829
00:50:16.126 --> 00:50:17.711
Oh. oh. but before we go...

830
00:50:18.503 --> 00:50:20.422
I want to show you something super cool.

831
00:50:20.965 --> 00:50:22.842
- Okay?
- Clay. cut it out.

832
00:50:23.550 --> 00:50:25.094
Look at these lockers.

833
00:50:25.677 --> 00:50:27.221
They all look alike. right?

834
00:50:29.264 --> 00:50:30.099
Not this one.

835
00:50:32.559 --> 00:50:33.728
This one is special.

836
00:50:34.644 --> 00:50:36.563
It belonged to a girl who killed herself.

837
00:50:36.771 --> 00:50:37.981
Clay. come on.

838
00:50:38.065 --> 00:50:40.985
You see all these "don't kill yourself"
posters up on the wall?

839
00:50:41.110 --> 00:50:42.360
They weren't up before.

840
00:50:42.445 --> 00:50:44.780
They put them up
<i>because </i>she killed herself.

841
00:50:44.905 --> 00:50:45.905
And why did she do it?

842
00:50:45.989 --> 00:50:47.782
Because the kids here
treated her like shit!

843
00:50:47.867 --> 00:50:49.117
Jensen. that's enough.

844
00:50:49.242 --> 00:50:51.286
But no one wants to admit it.
so they paint over the bathrooms

845
00:50:51.369 --> 00:50:54.206
and put up a memorial. because that's
the kind of school that this is.

846
00:50:54.289 --> 00:50:56.916
Everyone is just so <i>nice</i>
until they drive you to kill yourself.

847
00:50:57.126 --> 00:50:59.085
And sooner or later.
the truth will come out.

848
00:51:01.130 --> 00:51:02.213
It's gonna come out.

849
00:51:06.802 --> 00:51:09.221
Right. Tony? Right? You know the truth.

850
00:51:09.637 --> 00:51:10.597
Clay.

851
00:51:12.349 --> 00:51:14.351
I think you should come with me right now.

852
00:51:15.686 --> 00:51:17.480
Get to class. everybody!

853
00:51:18.063 --> 00:51:19.648
All you. get to class.

854
00:51:22.943 --> 00:51:24.152
Welcome to Liberty High.

855
00:51:25.153 --> 00:51:26.155
Let's go.

856
00:51:35.956 --> 00:51:36.956
Okay.

857
00:51:38.250 --> 00:51:39.126
New game.
